<row_model_note>
ROW MODEL (authoritative — RESEARCH.md Decision 1): `spectra_metadata.parquet` holds FOUR
co-resident top-level struct columns (`spectrum`, `scan`, `precursor`, `selected_ion`), each an
independent table laid out at row position = that table's own ordinal and right-padded with
all-null rows up to the shared file row count. ALL FOUR struct columns have N rows, where
N = spectrum count (= 48 for small.RAW). `spectrum`/`scan` are present (def-level 1) on all N
rows; `precursor`/`selected_ion` are present on rows 0..M-1 (M = count of emitted MSn ordinals)
and NULL (def-level 0) on rows M..N-1. Linkage is by the `source_index` field, NEVER by row
position. CONTEXT.md's earlier "each row populates exactly one struct, the other three are null"
(row-disjoint) wording is SUPERSEDED by this note.
</row_model_note>

<objective>
Turn the thin `spectra_metadata.parquet` (currently a 3-field `spectrum` struct: index/id/time) into the
full packed-parallel table set, and populate the `mzpeak_index.json` `metadata{}` block plus the Parquet
footer KV. This clears the last expected `mzpeak-validate` error (`required facet 'scan' absent`) without
introducing a new one (cv_list must appear the moment CV-named columns do).

Purpose: META-01..05 + IDX-01..04 — emit rich `spectrum`, the required `scan` facet, and the MSn-only
`precursor`/`selected_ion` facets as four co-resident independent tables linked by `source_index`, with
all CV terms as CURIE-named columns; emit the file-level metadata (instrument configurations, software,
data processing, file description, cv_list) into both the index and the footer.

Output: extended `MzPeakParquet` (general nested level computer + list-of-struct write path), rewritten
`BuildMetadataFacet` + index/footer assembly in `MzPeakSpectrumWriter`, and NUnit locks. `mzpeak-validate
small.mzpeak` shows the `scan`-facet error GONE and cv_list present.
</objective>

